{
  "info": {
    "name": "OpenCASE API",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the OpenCASE CASE Provider & Management API.\n\n## Setup\n1. Set the `base_url` variable to your OpenCASE instance (default: `http://localhost:3000`)\n2. Set `tenant_id` to your tenant (e.g. `demo`)\n3. Use the **Get Access Token** request (under Auth) to obtain a Bearer token — it auto-saves to the `access_token` variable\n4. All authenticated endpoints inherit the Bearer token from the collection\n\n## Folders\n- **Auth** — Token requests (client_credentials, password grant)\n- **Public** — Unauthenticated endpoints (health, tenant lookup, discovery)\n- **CASE Provider v1p0** — Standard CASE 1.0 read endpoints\n- **CASE Provider v1p1** — Standard CASE 1.1 read endpoints\n- **Management › Tenants** — Tenant CRUD (requires `case.admin`)\n- **Management › CFPackages** — Framework create/import/delete/restore\n- **Management › CFDocuments** — Document update/delete\n- **Management › CFItems** — Item update/delete\n- **Management › CFAssociations** — Association update/delete\n- **Management › Licenses** — License listing\n- **Management › API Keys** — API key CRUD (requires `case.owner` or `case.admin`)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{access_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:3000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "keycloak_realm_url", "value": "http://localhost:3000/realms/opencase", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "tenant_id", "value": "demo", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_id", "value": "tenant-{{tenant_id}}", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_secret", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "username", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "password", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "doc_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "item_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "association_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "api_key_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Token requests against the Keycloak OIDC endpoint.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Token (client_credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Token received', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "client_credentials" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{client_id}}" },
                { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{client_secret}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_realm_url}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_realm_url}}"],
              "path": ["protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Obtain an access token using the `client_credentials` grant.\n\nSet `client_id` and `client_secret` from an API key. The token is auto-saved to the `access_token` collection variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Token (password grant)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Token received', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{client_id}}" },
                { "key": "username", "value": "{{username}}" },
                { "key": "password", "value": "{{password}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_realm_url}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_realm_url}}"],
              "path": ["protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Obtain an access token using the `password` grant (direct access).\n\nSet `username` and `password` for the user. The tenant's SPA client must have direct access grants enabled.\nThe token is auto-saved to the `access_token` collection variable."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "description": "Unauthenticated endpoints — no Bearer token required.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Simple health check.\n\nReturns `{ \"status\": \"ok\" }` if the server is running."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Tenant Lookup",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/public/tenant-lookup?email=admin@demo.local",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["public", "tenant-lookup"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "admin@demo.local", "description": "Email to look up" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Anti-enumeration tenant lookup. Always returns 202; includes `tenantId` only if the email matches a known user."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
